organic_results.title: The Wisconsin model of status attainment: A national replication with improved measures of ability and aspiration
organic_results.snippet: A 1972 follow-up of eleventh graders surveyed by Project Talent in 1960 yields results broadly similar to those reported by Sewell and Hauser for their Wisconsin follow-up and by Alexander, Eckland and Griffin for their EEO follow-up, suggesting that neither the geographic and educational restrictions of the Wisconsin survey nor the low response rate of the EEO systematically biases their conclusions. The Talent data also provide more detailed information on teenagers' cognitive skills and educational aspirations than the Wisconsin …
